# Memory Capture Rules

## After Every Significant Task
1. Update .ohc/notepad.md:
   - What was completed
   - What was NOT completed (and why)
   - What the next person needs to know

2. If a project gotcha was discovered:
   - Append to .ohc/PROJECT.md under Known Gotchas
   - Format: `- [YYYY-MM-DD] <description> → WORKAROUND: <solution>`

3. If a novel pattern emerged:
   - Write to .ohc/skills/<pattern-name>.md as a draft skill
   - Keep it under 100 lines — just the pattern and when to use it
   - RETRO will review and promote if valid

## After RETRO Workflow
- Promote confirmed skills via `ohc skill promote <name>`
- For Cursor-specific learnings: use /Generate Cursor Rules
- Update ~/.ohc/USER.md if a personal preference was discovered

## Research Cache (cross-session)
Context7/Brave/GitHub doc fetches persist to .ohc/research/<library>--<topic>.md.
- Lookup before fetching: `require('./scripts/research').lookup(lib, topic)`.
- On fetch: `research.save({library, topic, payload, source, version})`.
- After code built on that research lands: `ohc research verify <library> <topic> <commit-sha>`.
- Default TTL 30d; `on-session-end.js` prunes stale entries.

## Team Artifacts (parallel workers)
When running as a `/team` worker, DO NOT append to .ohc/notepad.md directly —
concurrent writes race. Instead:
- Per-worker notes: .ohc/state/team/<id>/workers/<name>/notes.md
- Structured result: .ohc/state/team/<id>/workers/<name>/RESULT.json
  `{status, tests:{passed,failed,skipped}, files_changed, artifacts, notes, completedAt}`
The orchestrator refuses to advance past team-exec without every RESULT.json.

## Cross-Session Memory
notepad.md is read at session start. Write it for a teammate, not yourself.
Avoid agent jargon. Use plain language.
